# Vitest and Nuxt testing (repo-specific)

Official reference: [Nuxt 4 — Testing](https://nuxt.com/docs/4.x/getting-started/testing).

## Commands and config files

- **`pnpm test`** uses **`vitest.config.ts`** (`TZ=UTC vitest --run --config vitest.config.ts`).
- **`pnpm test:crypto`** runs **`vitest.crypto.config.ts`**: Hash/Jwt/Rsa service tests listed in **`vitestSlowTestExcludes`** (slow bcrypt work; not part of default `pnpm test`).
- **`vitest.config.all.ts`** only re-exports `vitest.config.ts` for backwards compatibility; prefer **`vitest.config.ts`** for new references.
- Coverage: **`vitest.config.coverage.ts`** (same project split + coverage reporters/options).

## Vitest projects (required pattern here)

Do **not** set global `test.environment: 'nuxt'` for the entire suite (slow; hybrid-env pitfalls per Nuxt docs).

- **`node`** project: `environment: 'node'`. Include/exclude globs: **`vitest.test-globs.ts`** (`vitestNodeTestIncludes`, `vitestNodeProjectExcludes`). The node project **excludes** `tests/nuxt/**` and `**/*.nuxt.{test,spec}.ts` so those files run only under the Nuxt project.
- **`nuxt`** project: built with **`defineVitestProject`** from `@nuxt/test-utils/config`. Includes **`tests/nuxt/**/*.test.ts`** and **`**/*.nuxt.{test,spec}.ts`** — use for composables/pages/plugins that need **`useNuxtApp`**, auto-imports, or full Nuxt pipeline.

## `~/` resolution in Vitest

Aliases are centralized in **`vitest.resolve-aliases.ts`** (`vitestResolveAliases`, **`vitestAliasLayer`**). Each Vitest subproject merges **`vitestAliasLayer`** via **`mergeConfig` from `vite`** — root-level `resolve.alias` alone is **not** reliably applied to multi-project runs.

## Nuxt app (`nuxt.config.ts`)

- **`@nuxt/test-utils/module`** is registered in **`modules`** (DevTools Vitest integration when DevTools are enabled).
- **`typescript.tsConfig.include`** includes paths for **`tests/nuxt`** (relative to generated `.nuxt/tsconfig.json`, per Nuxt docs) so TS/editor resolve Nuxt test dirs.

## Package versions

- **`@nuxt/test-utils` v3.x** matches **Vitest 3** currently in use. **`@nuxt/test-utils` v4+** declares a peer on **`vitest ^4.0.2`** — upgrade Vitest and test-utils together when moving to that stack.

## Agent policy

Test add/run policy lives in **`05-workflow-execution.mdc`** (do not add, modify, or run tests unless the user asks).
